<br>
<big style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 153);">About
the Modeling - COGRIM</span></big><br>
Based on the assumption that the expression levels of regulated genes
are affected by the expression levels of regulators, the first level of
our model incorporates our gene expression data by specifying the
observed gene log-expression g<small><small>it</small></small> as a
linear function of TF gene log-expression f<small><small>jt</small></small>
,<br>
<br>
&nbsp;<span style=""><img style="width: 148px; height: 45px;"
 src="index_files/image003.png" v:shapes="_x0000_s1027" title="" alt=""></span><br>
<br>
C<small>ij</small>: indicator variable for whether or not gene i is
regulated by TF j; where C<small><small>ij</small></small> = 1 if gene
i is regulated by TF j or 0 otherwise<br>
g<small><small>it</small></small>: expression levels for gene i in
state t: g<small><small>it</small></small>&nbsp; i = 1, . . . ,N; t =
1, . . . , T; where there are N genes and T states (or tissues)<br>
f<small><small>jt</small></small> : expression levels for TF j in state
t: f<small><small>jt</small></small> j = 1, . . . , J; t = 1, . . . ,
T; where there are transcription&nbsp; factors and T states ( or
tissues)<br>
&nbsp;<span style=""><img
 style="border: 0px solid ; width: 15px; height: 18px;"
 src="index_files/image006.png" v:shapes="_x0000_i1137" title="" alt="">
</span>: baseline expression for gene I in absence of known TFs ( ie.
Cij = 0 for all j)<br>
&nbsp;<span style=""><img
 style="border: 0px solid ; width: 18px; height: 19px;"
 src="index_files/image009.png" v:shapes="_x0000_i1136" title="" alt=""></span>:
effect of TF j on gene expression<br>
<br>
Each TF j has a single effect (bj) on the expression of gene i, which
does not take into account the biological reality that expression is
often the result of synergistic or antagonistic binding of multiple
TFs. We acknowledge these synergistic relationships by including
interaction terms in our linear model:<br>
<br>
<span style=""><img style="width: 287px; height: 49px;"
 src="index_files/image012.png" v:shapes="_x0000_s1028" title="" alt=""></span><br>
<br>
where we now have additional coefficients&nbsp; <span style=""><img
 style="border: 0px solid ; width: 17px; height: 18px;"
 v:shapes="_x0000_i1139" src="index_files/image017.png" title="" alt=""></span>
that can be interpreted as the synergistic (or antagonistic) effect of
both TFs j and k binding together to the same upstream region (in
addition to the effects of TF j or k binding in isolation).<br>
<br>
